?def: A mission is a named activity for some purpose@en
A mission that gather scientific data
An instrument is a physical object that can be used to collect data.
A PDS 4 collection where the collection_type is \Data\""

A data parameter is any characteristic that can help in understanding data content. That is, a parameter is a data element that is useful, or critical, when identifying  or describing the content of a data object.@en
A data product service in the GeneLab repository
A platform is a physical object to which an instrument is attached or in which it is contained.
A NASA mission is a mission led or funded by NASA@en
Something observable that happened at a given time and place
A plan for a coordinated set of actions and observations designed to generate data, with the ultimate goal of discovery or hypothesis testing.
An assay is an investigative (analytic) procedure for qualitatively assessing or quantitatively measuring the presence, amount, or functional activity of a target entity.
Any procedure that involves testing or manipulating a sample or subject in a laboratory setting
